 237:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****   @verbatim
 238:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****  ===============================================================================
 239:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            ##### Initialization and de-initialization functions #####
 240:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****  ===============================================================================
 241:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..]
 242:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****       This section provides functions allowing to configure the internal and external oscillators
 243:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (HSE, HSI, LSE, MSI, LSI, PLL, CSS and MCO) and the System busses clocks (SYSCLK, AHB, APB1
 244:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****        and APB2).
 245:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 246:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..] Internal/external clock and PLL configuration
 247:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) HSI (high-speed internal): 16 MHz factory-trimmed RC used directly or through
 248:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              the PLL as System clock source.
 249:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 250:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) MSI (Multiple Speed Internal): Its frequency is software trimmable from 100KHZ to 48MH
 251:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              It can be used to generate the clock for the USB FS or USB OTG FS (48 MHz).
 252:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              The number of flash wait states is automatically adjusted when MSI range is updated wi
 253:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              HAL_RCC_OscConfig() and the MSI is used as System clock source.
 254:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 255:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) LSI (low-speed internal): 32 KHz low consumption RC used as IWDG and/or RTC
 256:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              clock source.
 257:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccQQjroF.s 			page 6


 258:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) HSE (high-speed external): 4 to 48 MHz crystal oscillator used directly or
 259:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              through the PLL as System clock source. Can be used also optionally as RTC clock sourc
 260:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 261:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) LSE (low-speed external): 32.768 KHz oscillator used optionally as RTC clock source.
 262:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 263:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) PLL (clocked by HSI, HSE or MSI) providing up to three independent output clocks:
 264:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The first output is used to generate the high speed system clock (up to 80MHz).
 265:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The second output is used to generate the clock for the USB FS or USB OTG FS (48 MH
 266:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 the random analog generator (<=48 MHz) and the SDMMC1 (<= 48 MHz).
 267:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The third output is used to generate an accurate clock to achieve
 268:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 high-quality audio performance on SAI interface.
 269:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 270:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) PLL2 (clocked by HSI, HSE or MSI) providing up to three independent output clocks:
 271:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The first output is used to generate SAR ADC1 clock.
 272:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The second output is used to generate the clock for the USB Fs or USB OTG FS (48 MH
 273:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 the random analog generator (<=48 MHz) and the SDMMC1 (<= 48 MHz).
 274:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The Third output is used to generate an accurate clock to achieve
 275:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 high-quality audio performance on SAI interface.
 276:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 277:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) PLL3 (clocked by HSI , HSE or MSI) providing up to two independent output clocks:
 278:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The first output is used to generate SAR ADC4 clock.
 279:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) The second  output is used to generate an accurate clock to achieve
 280:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 high-quality audio performance on SAI interface.
 281:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 282:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) CSS (Clock security system): once enabled, if a HSE clock failure occurs
 283:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****             (HSE used directly or through PLL as System clock source), the System clock
 284:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              is automatically switched to HSI and an interrupt is generated if enabled.
 285:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              The interrupt is linked to the Cortex-M4 NMI (Non-Maskable Interrupt)
 286:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              exception vector.
 287:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 288:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) MCO (microcontroller clock output): used to output MSI, LSI, HSI, LSE, HSE or
 289:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              main PLL clock (through a configurable prescaler) on PA8 pin.
 290:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 291:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..] System, AHB and APB busses clocks configuration
 292:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) Several clock sources can be used to drive the System clock (SYSCLK): MSI, HSI,
 293:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              HSE and main PLL.
 294:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              The AHB clock (HCLK) is derived from System clock through configurable
 295:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              prescaler and used to clock the CPU, memory and peripherals mapped
 296:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              on AHB bus (DMA, GPIO...). APB1 (PCLK1) and APB2 (PCLK2) clocks are derived
 297:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              from AHB clock through configurable prescalers and used to clock
 298:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              the peripherals mapped on these busses. You can use
 299:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              "HAL_RCC_GetSysClockFreq()" function to retrieve the frequencies of these clocks.
 300:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 301:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          -@- All the peripheral clocks are derived from the System clock (SYSCLK) except:
 302:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 303:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (+@) SAI: the SAI clock can be derived either from a specific PLL (PLL2) or (PLL3) or
 304:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 from an external clock mapped on the SAI_CKIN pin.
 305:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 You have to use HAL_RCCEx_PeriphCLKConfig() function to configure this clock.
 306:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (+@) RTC: the RTC clock can be derived either from the LSI, LSE or HSE clock
 307:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 divided by 2 to 31.
 308:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 You have to use __HAL_RCC_RTC_ENABLE() and HAL_RCCEx_PeriphCLKConfig() function
 309:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 to configure this clock.
 310:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (+@) USB FS, USB OTG FS, SDMMC1 and RNG: USB OTG FS or USB FS requires a frequency equal
 311:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 to work correctly, while the SDMMC1 and RNG peripherals require a frequency
 312:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 equal or lower than to 48 MHz. This clock is derived of the main PLL or PLL2
 313:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 through PLLQ divider. You have to enable the peripheral clock and use
 314:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 HAL_RCCEx_PeriphCLKConfig() function to configure this clock.
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccQQjroF.s 			page 7


 315:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (+@) IWDG clock which is always the LSI clock.
 316:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 317:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 318:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (+) The maximum frequency of the SYSCLK, HCLK, PCLK1 and PCLK2 is 80 MHz.
 319:Drivers/STM32U5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32u5xx_hal_rcc.c ****              The clock source frequency should be adapted depending on the device voltage range
